rComments: Fantastic prof. Genuinely made me love political theory. His lectures are informative and enjoyable. His tests and papers were very straightforward and the exam was exactly what he said he would be. He is my favourite professor. Would HIGHLY recommend.

What a fabulous lecturer. Alumni Hall is a terrible place to have a class, but Carvounas actually made it worth it. Every lecture was like a story, and political theory became suddenly understandable. Some profs have a tendency to give their interpretation of a philosopher's work - not this dude.
Simply the best
Amazing lecturer, he simplifies topics and explains the course material really well and makes it easy to understand.

Best professor I have ever had at u of t! He simplifies and explains the texts extremely well and can even make some of the most confusing points interesting and easy to understand. I recommend taking any of his courses whether you are in political science, or would just like to have him as a prof!
Such an amazing prof. NICE to look at, nice to listen to, and he answers any questions you have. His lectures were some of the best I've had at UOT

Carvounas made POL320 way better than it could have been with another professor.  His lectures are very helpful for tests and assignments but they can be hard to listen to because he just speaks with no aids for the entire lecture.  Can repeat himself, but he does it to ensure that you understand what's important.  Makes hard material easy to grasp

This course was truly a learning experience. The topic was fascinating (Ancient Greece- from a Political Perspective).  What was more amazing were the concepts of politics that affect our daily lives to this very day. The laws that govern our lives were formed by politicians millenia ago. The Prof really relives this era during the lectures. A+
Such a beautiful man. Also, the best class I have taken thus far. His lectures, although sometimes a lot for the brain to take in, are really engaging and he makes the texts easy to understand
Great prof. Also nice to look at.

Hot and he's received his BA and MA from UCLA Berkely. He's one of the best professor's I have had. His test's are really straightforward if you go over his material and do the readings. Attending his class is almost mandatory because he hints at the important material.

The best Prof I have ever had, dreaded taking political theory until I took this class. Such and amazing,enigmatic,and passionate prof. Plus he`s really hot and tall. I will miss those suits he wear`s.

Engaging, enthusiastic lecturer.  Tests and assignments relatively straightforward.  Exam was a little difficult (given a list of random quotes from over 7 books and had to provide the title/author and definition).  Overall though, he's a great prof
Simply the best! We need more professors like him at the U of T.

Carvounas is one of most animated lecturers I've had yet.  His lectures are engaging and provide a clear and overview of the material.  He does not respond to feedback on the course as that would mean having to make changes (he recycles his material) starts lates, ends early and starts lecture with a recap of the past lecture for 15-20 mins.
Thought he looked cute... till I saw him up close -- under bright sunlight.
A beautiful, beautiful man.

Through all my years at University there has not been a single prof I have liked. I just don't like Profs period! This Prof does not fit that mold. The ONLY prof I've ever liked and respect. Was considering leaving , all I can say is please stay for the sake of us students.
The best class I've taken at U of T.  His lecture style is engaging and it keeps you interested.  Anyone who can make Hegel that interesting deserves praise.

Great Prof, really knows what he is talking about, 3 tests , an essay. and obviously a final exam so the workload was a little higher than what ive seen thus far in 300 series pol courses. but other than that, passionate prof and makes the class worth it, interesting texts as well

I don't think you can get a better professor.  Especially when talking about modern philosophers. He makes the topics so understandable and uses a down-to-earth approach when lecturing.  He doesn't go over your head to prove that he knows something you don't.  His goal is to make you understand and he does a great job of doing that.
No Comments

I took this course over the summer, and it was a great experience. He made theoretical concepts clear and easy to understand and his lecture style was relaxed yet engaging. He didn't even seem to use notes, he just lectured! and passionately!
Amazing Prof.

how come ppl thinks hes sooo hot...hes a professor! not great looking...just a regular professor. easy class tho

Carvounas ohhh carvounas, the hottest professor alive. He is extremely smart, enthusiastic and SEXY. He helps with any problems one might have in his course, even if it means telling you the whole book in one office hour...and sitting in his office isnt so bad since he's yummy to look at. hhhmmm!

THE SEXIEST PROFESSOR EVER! He's also VERY helpful, smart, and you actually learn stuff in his classes that you will never forget - he applies meaning to what he teaches; making it much more effective. He is always interesting - you never get bored in his classes. He is simply the best professor in ALL aspects - especially sexiness *drool*
If you are ever stuck with having to take a stinky course like POLC74, make sure you take it with this guy!  I'm so glad he's back!! He actually makes political theory fun! What da..%@#%!*?

prof Carvounas is extremely helpful and has always given time to explain the contents in the texts required to read.  hes the hottest prof ive ever had and i love his enthusiastic teaching b/c he allows the boring material come to life,everytime i do course selection i check if hes teaching, if so, im definitely in that class!
So incredibly smart, and he clearly gets the material across.  Also, he is one of the sexiest men I have ever laid eyes on...it's hard not to pay attention in class!

Easy class.  No essays. Just go to class and you pass.  Pretty cool Prof.  He's so smart, it makes me want to bang him!
He is the best teacher that I have ever had
teaches with the greatest enthusiasm and passion for the subject..motivates people to do well in hard-ass courses like pol 200! and he's got looks to top it off too ;) simply the best!

An excellent example of what a professor should be.He knew what he was talking about-is extremely knowledgeable and actually makes you think about stuff and relate it to the world in which you are living in. AND, the sexiest professor I have come across thus far!
A great teacher- an asset to his profession.
a very good prof but also very rude and cocky

His passion for teaching is beyond explanation, something you can only experience for yourself. It's absurd to think this 'great' university let such a phenomenal prof go. He will be remembered, and he will be missed.

Great prof. Easy to understand, and uses applicable examples. Makes often boring content come to life. If you're worried about this course, try and take it with Carvounas, you'll be glad that you did.

Carvounas teaches with a passion that is contagious.  One of (if not) the most talented, knowledgeable, and, it has to be said, best looking profs I've ever had.  I only wish the lectures were longer!
The best prof i hav ever had, very intelligent and interestingits a shame that he isnt teaching at utsc n e more if n e one has the chance take his course!!! great prof great man

interesting, thought-provoking and inspiring. His classes are a pleasure to attend and his insights are relevant to consumer culture
cool prof., easygoing, good lectures
